</header> <p>
Prayer for All Saints Day
</p>

 <p>
Lord,
</p>

 <p>
We search for heroes <br></br>
among the rich, powerful, <br></br>
strong and proud â€” <br></br>
those who look more <br></br>
like the crucifiers <br></br>
than the crucified. <br></br></p>

 <p>
But on this day, <br></br>
we give thanks <br></br>
for those for whom <br></br>
loving is more important <br></br>
than being loved, <br></br>
and faithfulness more <br></br>
dear than fame. <br></br></p>

 <p>
Not our idols, <br></br>
instead, your saints. <br></br></p>

 <p>
 <i>Amen</i>
</p>








